-- Nissan to recall nearly 500,000 March cars in Japan
-- 
-- Thu Dec 6, 2012 1:10am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/12/06/us-nissan-recall-idUSBRE8B508G20121206

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Nissan Motor Co Ltd ( 7201.T ) intends to recall 498,793 March/Micra hatchbacks in Japan to fix a problem with the rear combination light. 
 No accidents or injuries have been reported due to the fault, which only occurred in cars sold in Japan, a Nissan spokesman said. The company did not disclose any estimate of the cost of the recalls. (This story corrects to rear combination light from rear cabin light) (Reporting by Kentaro Sugiyama and  James Topham ; Editing by  Michael Watson )